Ghana’s Currency Unchanged in Trading Against U.S. Dollar

-- B y   J a s o n   M c L u r e
-- 
2011-04-04T14:37:20Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-04/ghana-s-currency-unchanged-in-trading-against-u-s-dollar.html
Ghana ’s currency, the cedi, was
unchanged in trading against the U.S. dollar today.  The currency of the world’s second-biggest cocoa producer
traded at 1.5075 per dollar at 2:04 p.m. in Accra, the same rate
as at the close of business April 1.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jason McLure in Accra at 
 jmclure@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 